{
  "text": "BoNT/A cleaves SNAP-25 at residue 197 to generate a membrane bound NH 2 -terminal SNAP-25 fragment, while BoNT/E removes a larger C terminus region of the protein by cleaving SNAP-25 at residue 180. The 17 amino acids between the cleavage sites for BoNT/A and BoNT/E are known to be required for high affinity binding of SNAP-25 to syntaxin 1 [CITATION_1] , for ternary complex formation with VAMP-2 and syntaxin 1 [CITATION_2] , for Ca 2+ -triggered membrane fusion [CITATION_3] and Ca 2+ -dependent synaptotagmin binding [CITATION_4] . In addition, the C-terminal region of SNAP-25 between BoNT/A and BoNT/E cleavage sites is also required for SNAP-25 modulation of voltage gated calcium currents [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "15653073",
    "[CITATION_2]": "45690449",
    "[CITATION_3]": "24607292",
    "[CITATION_4]": "10184193",
